isn't just there for passes,

00:09:32.655 --> 00:09:34.240 position:50% align:center
so we need to be careful.

00:09:36.034 --> 00:09:37.285 position:50% align:center
Got it.

00:09:37.285 --> 00:09:39.287 position:50% align:center
Okay! I'm depending on you!

00:09:42.123 --> 00:09:44.459 position:50% align:center
You are so cool, Yasunari-<i>kun</i>!

00:09:47.170 --> 00:09:50.173 position:50% align:center
Yasunari-<i>kun</i>?! What's wrong?

00:09:50.173 --> 00:09:51.841 position:50% align:center
I want to see some videos.

00:09:51.841 --> 00:09:54.761 position:50% align:center
Oh! Yes! Of course!

00:09:54.761 --> 00:09:57.263 position:50% align:center
I apologize that it's so messy!

00:09:57.263 --> 00:09:58.556 position:50% align:center
What were you doing?

00:09:58.556 --> 00:10:01.434 position:50% align:center
Oh, I was watching everyone's matches...

00:10:01.434 --> 00:10:04.688 position:50% align:center
It gets this messy just by
watching some matches?

00:10:04.688 --> 00:10:05.814 position:50% align:center
Oh...

00:10:05.814 --> 00:10:08.525 position:50% align:center
Were you doing some analyzing?

00:10:08.525 --> 00:10:14.114 position:50% align:center
I-I was just trying to imitate it!
I watched the analyst do it before...

00:10:14.114 --> 00:10:18.910 position:50% align:center
B-But I have the most data about
everyone from Maisagi High School,

00:10:18.910 --> 00:10:22.747 position:50% align:center
so I thought I could do some analyzing myself...

00:10:22.747 --> 00:10:24.958 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry. I did something unnecessary...

00:10:24.958 --> 00:10:26.876 position:50% align:center
--Me...
--Huh?

00:10:26.876 --> 00:10:28.294 position:50% align:center
Have any of me?

00:10:28.294 --> 00:10:30.505 position:50% align:center
I-I do.

00:10:30.505 --> 00:10:31.339 position:50% align:center
Show me.

00:10:31.339 --> 00:10:33.258 position:50% align:center
B-But...

00:10:33.258 --> 00:10:34.926 position:50% align:center
Just show me.

00:10:36.720 --> 00:10:42.350 position:50% align:center
This isn't all of it! And my analysis
may be wrong in the first place!

00:10:42.350 --> 00:10:44.644 position:50% align:center
No, it's right.

00:10:44.644 --> 00:10:47.063 position:50% align:center
It hurts because it's right.

00:10:47.063 --> 00:10:50.358 position:50% align:center
B-But you are so cool, Yasunari-<i>kun</i>!

00:10:50.358 --> 00:10:51.818 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:10:51.818 --> 00:10:54.487 position:50% align:center
Your plays are so cool, Yasunari-<i>kun</i>!

00:10:54.487 --> 00:10:56.823 position:50% align:center
Natsusa-<i>san</i>'s plays look pretty.

00:10:56.823 --> 00:10:59.367 position:50% align:center
Seiichirou-<i>san</i>'s look uniform.

00:10:59.367 --> 00:11:01.244 position:50% align:center
Ibuki-<i>san</i>'s plays are always genius.

00:11:01.244 --> 00:11:04.205 position:50% align:center
Saitou-<i>kun</i>'s plays look heavy.

00:11:04.205 --> 00:11:07.792 position:50% align:center
And Yasunari-<i>kun</i>'s look cool!

00:11:07.792 --> 00:11:11.671 position:50% align:center
That is something that can't
be shown through analysis!

00:11:14.257 --> 00:11:18.345 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry. I guess I don't make sense.

00:11:18.345 --> 00:11:21.181 position:50% align:center
I don't get it, but...

00:11:21.181 --> 00:11:22.724 position:50% align:center
Well...

00:11:22.724 --> 00:11:24.893 position:50% align:center
Well?

00:11:24.893 --> 00:11:26.603 position:50% align:center
No, it's nothing.

00:11:26.603 --> 00:11:29.481 position:50% align:center
Huh? What is it? Now it's bothering me!

00:11:29.481 --> 00:11:31.066 position:50% align:center
I said it's nothing!

00:11:31.066 --> 00:11:33.651 position:50% align:center
But I might have made you feel bad!

00:11:33.651 --> 00:11:34.611 position:50% align:center
You didn't!

00:11:34.611 --> 00:11:36.196 position:50% align:center
--But--!
--It's fine!

00:11:36.196 --> 00:11:38.239 position:50% align:center
More importantly! Madoka Hongou!

00:11:38.239 --> 00:11:39.074 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:11:39.074 --> 00:11:43.078 position:50% align:center
D-Did you analyze Madoka Hongou-<i>san</i>?

00:11:43.078 --> 00:11:44.788 position:50% align:center
He's also from Maisagi High School...

00:11:44.788 --> 00:11:50.627 position:50% align:center
Oh, yes. I didn't analyze his plays
during high school as much, but...

00:11:50.627 --> 00:11:53.463 position:50% align:center
I have done some analysis
on him in his college years.

00:11:53.463 --> 00:11:55.423 position:50% align:center
Since he's on an enemy team...

00:11:55.423 --> 00:12:00.804 position:50% align:center
When the backs charge forward,
he always stands in front of the goal.

00:12:00.804 --> 00:12:03.932 position:50% align:center
We won't be able to get a try
if we can't take care of him.

00:12:03.932 --> 00:12:08.269 position:50% align:center
Can you think up a strategy using the
information you got of Madoka-<i>san </i>and me?

00:12:08.269 --> 00:12:10.689 position:50% align:center
L-Let me try!

00:12:16.778 --> 00:12:18.154 position:50% align:center
Yasunari!

00:12:21.282 --> 00:12:25.662 position:50% align:center
Madoka-<i>san </i>doesn't have any particular habits.

00:12:25.662 --> 00:12:28.832 position:50% align:center
I don't know if he does it on purpose or not,

00:12:28.832 --> 00:12:31.167 position:50% align:center
but he defends by matching
the movements of his opponents.

00:12:31.167 --> 00:12:34.421 position:50% align:center
That's why he's so hard to get past.

00:12:34.421 --> 00:12:37.424 position:50% align:center
But because of that, we have the initiative!

00:12:45.807 --> 00:12:49.227 position:50% align:center
First, you usually hold the ball
with your left hand,

00:12:49.227 --> 00:12:53.231 position:50% align:center
but please switch it to your right
when you want to pass Madoka-<i>san</i>.

00:12:55.692 --> 00:12:57.569 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:12:57.569 --> 00:13:01.948 position:50% align:center
Then, you usually swerve from the right,

00:13:01.948 --> 00:13:04.117 position:50% align:center
so swerve from the other direction.

00:13:07.203 --> 00:13:10.165 position:50% align:center
You might lose some time doing the actions,

00:13:10.165 --> 00:13:13.418 position:50% align:center
but you'll definitely be harder to read!

00:13:14.878 --> 00:13:16.921 position:50% align:center
All right!

00:13:16.921 --> 00:13:19.174 position:50% align:center
As I thought, he's so cool!

00:13:19.174 --> 00:13:20.425 position:50% align:center
Good job!

00:13:20.425 --> 00:13:22.677 position:50% align:center
You did it!

00:13:22.677 --> 00:13:25.555 position:50% align:center
Looks like your analysis was spot on.

00:13:25.555 --> 00:13:28.475 position:50% align:center
N-No! Not at all!

00:13:28.475 --> 00:13:34.898 position:50% align:center
If you had told us earlier, we might
have won the last two matches.

00:13:34.898 --> 00:13:36.024 position:50% align:center
Natsusa...

00:13:36.024 --> 00:13:39.486 position:50% align:center
I'll have you work your butt off
when we get to nationals.

00:13:39.486 --> 00:13:41.488 position:50% align:center
Y-Yes!

00:13:41.488 --> 00:13:43.948 position:50% align:center
Yasunari-<i>kun</i>.

00:13:43.948 --> 00:13:47.660 position:50% align:center
You've really grown.

00:13:47.660 --> 00:13:49.454 position:50% align:center
Thank you very much.

00:13:49.454 --> 00:13:52.540 position:50% align:center
I've gotten some good comrades.

00:13:54.459 --> 00:13:58.463 position:50% align:center
Really... He's grown...

00:14:05.220 --> 00:14:08.264 position:50% align:center
We've finally managed to turn the tables.

00:14:10.058 --> 00:14:13.228 position:50% align:center
All right! We need to stall for time and escape!

00:14:13.228 --> 00:14:15.438 position:50% align:center
Don't give the other team the ball!

00:14:15.438 --> 00:14:17.857 position:50% align:center
It's nice to see such honesty!

00:14:20.443 --> 00:14:21.945 position:50% align:center
You aren't an enemy to me.

00:14:21.945 --> 00:14:23.363 position:50% align:center
What?!

00:14:32.872 --> 00:14:33.873 position:50% align:center
Ethan!

00:14:38.461 --> 00:14:39.921 position:50% align:center
I'll stop him!

00:14:47.512 --> 00:14:49.514 position:50% align:center
Try!

00:14:49.514 --> 00:14:51.599 position:50% align:center
At a time like this!

00:14:55.311 --> 00:14:56.354 position:50% align:center
Ethan.

00:14:59.733 --> 00:15:01.901 position:50% align:center
Don't involve the team
in your personal issues!

00:15:01.901 --> 00:15:04.612 position:50% align:center
There's a limit to being selfish!

00:15:04.612 --> 00:15:07.198 position:50% align:center
No. No one wants to hear that from you.

00:15:07.198 --> 00:15:09.200 position:50% align:center
You quit the team without a word.

00:15:09.200 --> 00:15:10.160 position:50% align:center
Exactly.

00:15:10.160 --> 00:15:12.245 position:50% align:center
You ruined it!

00:15:12.245 --> 00:15:15.373 position:50% align:center
Right. And Ibuki is just scared!

00:15:15.373 --> 00:15:16.916 position:50% align:center
No! I'm not scared at all!

00:15:16.916 --> 00:15:20.837 position:50% align:center
You look scared to me. You're holding back.

00:15:20.837 --> 00:15:23.381 position:50% align:center
You've been doing good.

00:15:23.381 --> 00:15:28.845 position:50% align:center
Everyone knows you've been giving your all
to the team these last few months.

00:15:28.845 --> 00:15:31.723 position:50% align:center
You don't owe anyone anything.

00:15:31.723 --> 00:15:33.516 position:50% align:center
Aren't we a team?

00:15:47.447 --> 00:15:48.907 position:50% align:center
All right! Miss!

00:15:52.410 --> 00:15:53.828 position:50% align:center
It went in?!

00:15:58.625 --> 00:16:01.628 position:50% align:center
This is the last play.

00:16:01.628 --> 00:16:05.090 position:50% align:center
If we falter on the attack here, it's over...

00:16:09.969 --> 00:16:13.348 position:50% align:center
There's something I've wanted.

00:16:13.348 --> 00:16:17.477 position:50% align:center
I want to give my all to someone
without the calculations.

00:16:17.477 --> 00:16:22.148 position:50% align:center
I want someone to give me their all
without any calculation.

00:16:26.945 --> 00:16:28.321 position:50% align:center
Yasunari!

00:16:32.325 --> 00:16:34.786 position:50% align:center
To give myself unconditionally.

00:16:34.786 --> 00:16:38.456 position:50% align:center
It's probably something called love.

00:16:38.456 --> 00:16:43.753 position:50% align:center
Something that people born into
a loving family had at birth...

00:16:45.088 --> 00:16:48.008 position:50% align:center
I desperately wanted something like that.

00:16:49.092 --> 00:16:50.468 position:50% align:center
Then!

00:16:50.468 --> 00:16:55.306 position:50% align:center
Natsusa and Sei-<i>chan</i>
will become your family!

00:16:56.933 --> 00:16:59.060 position:50% align:center
I want to tell my past self.

00:17:00.895 --> 00:17:02.731 position:50% align:center
It's all right.

00:17:02.731 --> 00:17:05.150 position:50% align:center
You'll definitely get it.

00:17:05.150 --> 00:17:12.991 position:50% align:center
As long as you don't give up,
you'll get it in a way you never imagined.

00:17:12.991 --> 00:17:14.617 position:50% align:center
So...

00:17:14.617 --> 00:17:16.828 position:50% align:center
Don't give up!

00:17:32.427 --> 00:17:34.679 position:50% align:center
Try!

00:17:34.679 --> 00:17:36.348 position:50% align:center
All right!

00:17:42.312 --> 00:17:43.938 position:50% align:center
No side.

00:17:53.740 --> 00:17:56.034 position:50% align:center
We did it, Ibuki!

00:18:00.914 --> 00:18:02.082 position:50% align:center
Hey.

00:18:03.166 --> 00:18:05.835 position:50% align:center
Get up already.

00:18:05.835 --> 00:18:07.045 position:50% align:center
Give me a hand.

00:18:07.045 --> 00:18:08.546 position:50% align:center
Don't be spoiled.

00:18:08.546 --> 00:18:11.508 position:50% align:center
More importantly! Ibuki!
You're bleeding too much!

00:18:11.508 --> 00:18:12.842 position:50% align:center
I think so, too.

00:18:12.842 --> 00:18:14.678 position:50% align:center
If I don't stop it quickly...

00:18:21.976 --> 00:18:23.353 position:50% align:center
Kazutaka!

00:18:25.105 --> 00:18:27.065 position:50% align:center
You better treat me to some grilled mea--

00:18:27.065 --> 00:18:28.650 position:50% align:center
--Ibuki!
--Ueoka!

00:18:28.650 --> 00:18:31.027 position:50% align:center
Ibuki is really gonna die...

00:18:37.534 --> 00:18:40.078 position:50% align:center
Don't cry from a single loss.

00:18:40.078 --> 00:18:43.081 position:50% align:center
We just need to crush them at nationals.

00:18:43.081 --> 00:18:47.085 position:50% align:center
That's right. Touma, don't cry.

00:18:47.085 --> 00:18:49.838 position:50% align:center
But even so...

00:18:49.838 --> 00:18:53.383 position:50% align:center
Losing really pumps the adrenaline!

00:18:53.383 --> 00:18:55.010 position:50% align:center
Natsusa-<i>san</i>!

00:19:00.390 --> 00:19:03.184 position:50% align:center
Why?

00:19:03.184 --> 00:19:07.188 position:50% align:center
Ow! Ow! It's painful!

00:19:07.188 --> 00:19:11.818 position:50% align:center
It hurts. It's painful. I can't breathe...

00:19:11.818 --> 00:19:13.778 position:50% align:center
Don't do strenuous exercise.

00:19:13.778 --> 00:19:16.031 position:50% align:center
Huh? Why?

00:19:16.031 --> 00:19:17.949 position:50% align:center
Why would you say something like that?

00:19:17.949 --> 00:19:19.909 position:50% align:center
I want to play rugby!

00:19:19.909 --> 00:19:23.747 position:50% align:center
Won't you be alone?

00:19:23.747 --> 00:19:27.667 position:50% align:center
I will! Don't leave me behind!

00:19:31.379 --> 00:19:32.589 position:50% align:center
Why?!

00:19:32.589 --> 00:19:35.091 position:50% align:center
That's my number.

00:19:35.091 --> 00:19:37.302 position:50% align:center
I love rugby this much!

00:19:37.302 --> 00:19:39.971 position:50% align:center
I poured all of my heart into rugby!

00:19:39.971 --> 00:19:42.807 position:50% align:center
Why can't I play?!

00:19:47.354 --> 00:19:49.939 position:50% align:center
Sorry for the wait.

00:19:49.939 --> 00:19:52.692 position:50% align:center
Natsusa?

00:19:52.692 --> 00:19:59.449 position:50% align:center
Sorry for pretending like I couldn't see you
and for leaving you alone for so long.

00:19:59.449 --> 00:20:01.284 position:50% align:center
No...

00:20:01.284 --> 00:20:03.370 position:50% align:center
Is everything all right now?

00:20:03.370 --> 00:20:05.580 position:50% align:center
Yeah. It's all right.

00:20:05.580 --> 00:20:07.207 position:50% align:center
You won't cry?

00:20:07.207 --> 00:20:08.750 position:50% align:center
I might.

00:20:08.750 --> 00:20:11.044 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:20:11.044 --> 00:20:13.296 position:50% align:center
But I won't be hurt anymore.

00:20:13.296 --> 00:20:15.465 position:50% align:center
Like everyone else...

00:20:17.050 --> 00:20:19.094 position:50% align:center
I've gotten stronger.

00:20:19.094 --> 00:20:21.304 position:50% align:center
You worked hard.

00:20:21.304 --> 00:20:23.682 position:50% align:center
Thanks for waiting for me.

00:20:23.682 --> 00:20:25.308 position:50% align:center
No, it's fine.

00:20:25.308 --> 00:20:27.852 position:50% align:center
Can I stay with you again, Natsusa?

00:20:27.852 --> 00:20:28.728 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:20:28.728 --> 00:20:29.854 position:50% align:center
Really?!

00:20:29.854 --> 00:20:33.149 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I want you to stay with me.

00:20:33.149 --> 00:20:34.567 position:50% align:center
Come back home.

00:20:34.567 --> 00:20:36.069 position:50% align:center
Thank goodness!

00:20:53.586 --> 00:20:55.463 position:50% align:center
Welcome home.

